From 8277f8538b5d047295d31529123574b0d5c01729 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brian Cain <brian.cain@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Mar 2026 13:26:51 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 11/15] [compiler-rt] Fix struct_kernel_stat_sz for
 hexagon-linux-musl
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="utf-8"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Hexagon musl's struct stat is 152 bytes, not 128.  The extra 24 bytes
come from time64 fields (st_atim, st_mtim, st_ctim as struct timespec)
alongside the legacy 32-bit __st_atim32/__st_mtim32/__st_ctim32 and
two __unused padding words, defined in musl/arch/hexagon/bits/stat.h.

The incorrect size causes a static assertion failure when building
sanitizers:

  sanitizer_platform_limits_posix.cpp: error: static assertion failed
    struct_kernel_stat_sz == sizeof(struct stat)  (128 != 152)

Update the constant from 128 to 152.
---
 .../lib/sanitizer_common/sanitizer_platform_limits_posix.h      | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/compiler-rt/lib/sanitizer_common/sanitizer_platform_limits_posix.h b/compiler-rt/lib/sanitizer_common/sanitizer_platform_limits_posix.h
index 05ebee49f2ab..3a21d8ef5ac0 100644
--- a/compiler-rt/lib/sanitizer_common/sanitizer_platform_limits_posix.h
+++ b/compiler-rt/lib/sanitizer_common/sanitizer_platform_limits_posix.h
@@ -128,7 +128,7 @@ const unsigned struct_kernel_stat64_sz = 104;
 const unsigned struct_kernel_stat_sz = 128;
 const unsigned struct_kernel_stat64_sz = 0;  // RISCV64 does not use stat64
 #    elif defined(__hexagon__)
-const unsigned struct_kernel_stat_sz = 128;
+const unsigned struct_kernel_stat_sz = 152;
 const unsigned struct_kernel_stat64_sz = 0;
 #    elif defined(__loongarch__)
 const unsigned struct_kernel_stat_sz = 128;
-- 
